4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=\u30ef\u30fc\u30ca\u30fc \u30d6\u30e9\u30b6\u30fc\u30b9 \u516c\u5f0f\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30cd\u30eb|title=\u6620\u753b\u300e\u30cb\u30f3\u30b8\u30e3\u30d0\u30c3\u30c8\u30de\u30f3\u300f \u65e5\u672c\u7528\u30c8\u30ec\u30fc\u30e9\u30fc\uff1c\u516c\u958b\u65e5\u8ffd\u52a0ver\uff1e\u30102018\u5e746\u670815\u65e5\u5287\u5834\u516c\u958b\u3011|date=March 15, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J6jhuFxNQX8|accessdate=March 16, 2018|work=[[Warner Bros.]]|publisher=[[YouTube]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Batman Ninja Anime's English Trailer Reveals Dub Cast, Home Video Release|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-02-13/batman-ninja-anime-english-trailer-reveals-dub-cast-home-video-release/.127749|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=February 13, 2018|date=February 13, 2018|first=Karen|last=Ressler}}</ref>\n\n=== With other heroes ===\n====Theatrical ====\n* 2017: ''DC Super Heroes vs. Eagle Talon'', with [[Takayuki Yamada]] voicing Batman<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dc-taka.com/character/\u30d0\u30c3\u30c8\u30de\u30f3/|title=\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\u540d|website=dc-taka.com|language=Japanese|accessdate=April 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* 2018: ''[[Teen Titans Go! To the Movies]]'' with [[Jimmy Kimmel]] voicing Batman.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://screenrant.com/jimmy-kimmel-voice-batman-teen-titans-go-movie/|title=Jimmy Kimmel to Voice Batman in Teen Titans GO! Movie|last=Stauffer|first=Derek|work=Screen Rant|accessdate=November 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Direct-to-video====\n* 2008: ''[[Justice League: The New Frontier]]'', based on the [[DC: The New Frontier|comic of the same name]] with [[Jeremy Sisto]] voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://movieweb.com/jeremy-sisto-is-batman-in-justice-league-the-new-frontier/|title=Jeremy Sisto Is Batman in \u2018Justice League: The New Frontier\u2019|date=2008-02-18|website=Movieweb|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2009: ''[[Superman/Batman: Public Enemies]]'', based on the comic of the same name with Kevin Conroy voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dcanimated.com/WF/dcuam/publicenemies/backstage/conroy.php|title=The World's Finest - DC Universe - Superman / Batman: Public Enemies|website=dcanimated.com|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2010: ''[[Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths]]'', a loose adaptation of various DC comics with [[William Baldwin]] voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animesuperhero.com/william-baldwin-on-voicing-the-dark-knight-for-justice-league-crisis-on-two-earths/|title=William Baldwin on Voicing the Dark Knight for \"Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths\"|last=Liu|first=Ed|date=2009-12-17|website=Anime Superhero News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2010: ''[[Superman/Batman: Apocalypse]]'', based on ''Superman/Batman: The Supergirl from Krypton'' with Kevin Conroy voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.comicbookmovie.com/superman/kevin-conroy-interview-superman/batman-apocalypse-a22734|title=Kevin Conroy Interview: Superman/Batman Apocalypse|last=Under: \"Superman\"|first=EdGross {{!}} 9/17/2010 Filed|website=www.comicbookmovie.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2010: ''[[DC Super Friends|DC Super Friends: The Joker\u2019s Playhouse]]'', based on the [[Fisher-Price]] toyline with [[Daran Norris]] voicing Batman<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.voiceoverherald.com/many-voices-batman/|title=The Many Voices of Batman -|date=2014-10-20|website=Voice Over Talent Industry News|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2012: ''[[Justice League: Doom]]'', based on ''[[JLA: Tower of Babel]]'' with Kevin Conroy voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2599353/justice-league-doom-cast-nathan-fillion-kevin-conroy/|title='Justice League: Doom' Cast Includes Nathan Fillion, Kevin Conroy|last=Page|first=Splash|website=MTV News|language=en|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2013: ''[[Justice League: The Flashpoint Paradox]]'', based on ''[[Flashpoint (comics)|Flashpoint]]'' with [[Kevin McKidd]] voicing Batman<ref name=\":2\" />\n* 2014: ''[[JLA Adventures: Trapped in Time]]'', an original story with [[Diedrich Bader]] voicing Batman<ref name=\":2\" />\n* 2014: ''[[Justice League: War]]'', based on ''Justice League: Origin'' with Jason O'Mara voicing Batman<ref name=\":2\" />\n* 2014: ''[[Lego DC Comics: Batman Be-Leaguered|Lego DC Comics Super Heroes: Batman Be-Leaguered]]'' animated television special, with [[Troy Baker]] reprising his role as Batman from the Lego video games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/tv-shows/DC-Super-Heroes-Batman-Be-Leaguered/|title=DC Super Heroes Batman Be-Leaguered|website=Behind The Voice Actors|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2015: ''[[Justice League: Throne of Atlantis]]'', based on ''[[Throne of Atlantis]]'' with Jason O'Mara voicing Batman<ref name=\":2\" />\n* 2015: ''[[Justice League: Gods and Monsters]]'' with [[Michael C. Hall]] voicing a [[Kirk Langstrom]] version of Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/reviews/justice-league-gods-and-monsters-review-bluray-release-bruce-timm-1201546139/|title=Blu-Ray Review: \u2018Justice League: Gods and Monsters\u2019|last=Lowry|first=Brian|last2=Lowry|first2=Brian|date=2015-07-24|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2015: ''[[Lego DC Comics Super Heroes: Justice League vs. Bizarro League]]'', with Troy Baker reprising his role<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/exclusive-batman-gets-upstaged-in-dcs-lego-justice-league-vs-bizarro-league-clip/|title=EXCLUSIVE: Batman Gets Upstaged in DC's \"LEGO Justice League vs. Bizarro League\" Clip|date=2015-02-06|website=CBR|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2016: ''[[Lego DC Comics Super Heroes: Justice League \u2013 Cosmic Clash]]'', with Troy Baker reprising his role<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/nycc-lego-heroes-return-in-justice-league-cosmic-clash/|title=NYCC: LEGO Heroes Return in \"Justice League: Cosmic Clash\"|date=2015-10-11|website=CBR|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2019: ''[[Batman vs. Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]],'' with Troy Baker voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbr.com/batman-vs-tmnts-troy-baker-voicing-batman-joker/|title=Batman Vs. TMNT's Troy Baker on Voicing Both Batman & The Joker|date=2019-05-29|website=CBR|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2020: ''[[Superman: Red Son (film)|Superman: Red Son]]'', with Roger Craig Smith voicing Batman.\n\n=== ''The Lego Movie'' series ===\n* 2014: A [[Lego]]-themed version of Batman appears in ''[[The Lego Movie]]'', voiced by [[Will Arnett]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/will-arnett-the-lego-movie_n_4718599|title='LEGO Movie' Star Will Arnett On 'Arrested Development' Criticism|last=Rosen|first=Christopher|date=2014-02-03|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2017: The character receives his own spin-off film, ''[[The Lego Batman Movie]]'', voiced again by Arnett. This film takes place in a universe where all of the previous live-action films, as well as some animated series, have happened.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-lego-batman-will-arnett-2017-story.html|title=Will Arnett on the pressure of starring in 'The Lego Batman Movie' and the precious instrument that is his voice|date=2017-02-09|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n* 2019: Arnett reprised his role as Lego Batman in ''[[The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2019/02/06/lego-movie-2-arnett-explains-batman-superman-superfeud/2781912002/|title=Lego Batman feuds with Superman, falls in love in 'Lego Movie 2': Will Arnett explains why|last=Alexander|first=Bryan|website=USA TODAY|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n\n=== Other ===\n* 2008: ''[[Batman: Gotham Knight]]'', a collection of original shorts with Kevin Conroy voicing Batman<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.superherohype.com/features/96565-kevin-conroy-on-voicing-batman-gotham-knight|title=Kevin Conroy on Voicing Batman Gotham Knight|date=2008-05-14|website=SuperHeroHype|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref>\n\n==Recurring cast and characters==\n{{main|List of Batman films cast members}}\n{{Cast indicator|appeared=multiple \"franchises\" of Batman films|C}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:99%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:11.25%;\" | Character\n! [[Serial film|Serial]] films<br><small>(1943\u20131949)</small>\n! ''[[Batman (1966 film)|Batman]]''<br><small>(1966)</small>\n! [[Tim Burton]] / [[Joel Schumacher]] films<br><small>(1989\u20131997)</small>\n! ''[[The Dark Knight Trilogy]]''<br><small>(2005\u20132012)</small>\n! [[DC Extended Universe]]<br><small>(2016\u2013present)</small>\n! ''[[Joker (2019 film)|Joker]]''<br><small>(2019)</small>\n|-\n! [[Batman|Bruce Wayne<br>{{small|Batman}}]]\n| [[Lewis Wilson]]<hr>[[Robert Lowery (actor)|Robert Lowery]]\n| [[Adam West]]\n| [[Michael Keaton]]{{efn|Additionally, Charles Roskilly portrays a young Bruce Wayne in ''[[Batman (1989 film)|Batman]]'' (1989).}}<hr>[[Val Kilmer]]{{efn|Additionally, Ramsey Ellis portrays a young Bruce Wayne in ''[[Batman Forever]]''.}}<hr>[[George Clooney]]{{efn|Additionally, [[Eric Lloyd]] portrays a young Bruce Wayne in ''[[Batman & Robin (film)|Batman & Robin]]''.}}\n| [[Christian Bale]]{{efn|Additionally, [[Gus Lewis]] portrays a young Bruce Wayne in ''[[Batman Begins]]'', and in archival footage used in ''[[The Dark Knight Rises]]''.}}\n| [[Ben Affleck]]{{efn|Additionally, Brandon Spink portrays a young Bruce Wayne in ''[[Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice]]''.}}<hr>[[Robert Pattinson]]\n| [[Dante Pereira-Olson]]\n|-\n! [[Alfred Pennyworth]]\n| [[William Austin (actor)|William Austin]]<hr>Eric Wilton\n| [[Alan Napier]]\n| [[Michael Gough]]{{efn|Additionally, Jon Simmons portrays a young Bruce Wayne in ''[[Batman & Robin (film)|Batman & Robin]]''.}}\n| [[Michael Caine]]\n| [[Jeremy Irons]]<hr>[[Andy Serkis]]\n| [[Douglas Hodge]]\n|-\n! [[James Gordon (character)|James \"Jim\" Gordon]]\n| [[Lyle Talbot]]\n| [[Neil Hamilton (actor)|Neil Hamilton]]\n| [[Pat Hingle]]\n| [[Gary Oldman]]\n| [[J. K. Simmons]]<hr>[[Jeffrey Wright]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Robin (character)|Richard \"Dick\" Grayson<br>{{small|Robin}}]]\n| [[Douglas Croft]]<hr>[[Johnny Duncan (actor)|Johnny Duncan]]\n| [[Burt Ward]]\n| [[Chris O'Donnell]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Vicki Vale]]\n| [[Poni Adams|Jane Adams]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Kim Basinger]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Joker (character)|Joker]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Cesar Romero]]\n| [[Jack Nicholson]]{{efn|Additionally, Hugo E. Blick portrays a young Joker in ''[[Batman (1989 film)|Batman]]'' (1989).}}<hr>David U. Hodges\n| [[Heath Ledger]]\n| [[Jared Leto]]\n| [[Joaquin Phoenix]]\n|-\n! [[Catwoman|Selina Kyle <br>{{small|Catwoman}}]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Lee Meriwether]]\n| [[Michelle Pfeiffer]]\n| [[Anne Hathaway]]\n| [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Penguin (character)|Oswald Cobblepot<br>{{small|Penguin}}]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Burgess Meredith]]\n| [[Danny DeVito]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Colin Farrell]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Riddler]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Frank Gorshin]]\n| [[Jim Carrey]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Paul Dano]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Two-Face|Harvey Dent<br>{{small|Two-Face}}]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Billy Dee Williams]]{{ref|cameo|C}}<hr>[[Tommy Lee Jones]]\n| [[Aaron Eckhart]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Thomas Wayne]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| David Baxt<hr>Michael Scranton{{ref|cameo|C}}\n| [[Linus Roache]]\n| [[Jeffrey Dean Morgan]]\n| [[Brett Cullen]]\n|-\n! [[Martha Wayne]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| Sharon Holm<hr>Eileen Seeley{{ref|cameo|C}}\n| [[Sara Stewart]]\n| [[Lauren Cohan]]\n| Carrie Louise Putrello\n|-\n! Mayor of Gotham City\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Lee Wallace (actor)|Lee Wallace]]<hr>[[Michael Murphy (actor)|Michael Murphy]]<hr>[[George Wallace (American comedian)|George Wallace]]\n| [[N\u00e9stor Carbonell]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Sal Maroni]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| Dennis Paladino\n| [[Eric Roberts]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Bane (DC Comics)|Bane]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Robert Swenson]]{{efn|Additionally, Michael Reid MacKay portrays Antonio Diego in ''[[Batman & Robin (film)|Batman & Robin]]'', a serial killer who is ultimately transformed into Bane.}}\n| [[Tom Hardy]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Scarecrow|Jonathan Crane<br>{{small|Scarecrow}}]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Coolio]]\n| [[Cillian Murphy]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Carmine Falcone]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Tom Wilkinson]]\n| [[John Turturro]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|}\n\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n== Reception ==\nWith a total gross of over $4.99 billion at the global box office, the series is [[List of highest-grossing franchises and film series|eleventh highest-grossing film franchise]] of all time. Domestically, ''Batman'' films have grossed U.S. $2,783,118,504, making the franchise the fourth-highest-grossing film series in North America.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm|title=Box Office Mojo Movie Franchises Index Sorted by Total Gross|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=July 10, 2013}}</ref> Critical reception of the modern films has varied throughout its different eras. [[The Dark Knight (film)|''The Dark Knight'']], from [[Christopher Nolan]]'s trilogy, is considered [[List of films considered the best|one of the best superhero movies ever]], while two entries, ''Batman and Robin'' and ''Catwoman'' are considered [[List of films considered the worst|some of the worst]]. ''The Dark Knight Rises'' is the highest-grossing ''Batman'' movie, grossing $1,081,041,287 worldwide, while ''Batman and Robin'' is the lowest-grossing film to feature Batman, at $238,207,122 worldwide. Films in the series have earned three [[Academy Awards]] (Burton's ''Batman'' for Production Design and ''The Dark Knight'' for Sound Editing and posthumous Best Supporting Actor for [[Heath Ledger]]'s performance as the Joker), one [[BAFTAs|BAFTA]] (also for Ledger), and ten [[Saturn Awards]], which honor excellence in science fiction, horror, and fantasy.\n\nOf the 1980s and 1990s, Tim Burton's films received positive critical reviews for their return of the character to a more serious portrayal, though some felt that ''Batman Returns'' was too dark. Joel Schumacher's two films received mixed to negative reviews, particularly ''Batman and Robin'', which has the lowest aggregate scores out of any film in the series. Conversely, the films in Christopher Nolan's trilogy of the 2000s and 2010s have the highest scores on review aggregation websites of the live-action feature films with ''The Dark Knight'' receiving a 94% from [[Rotten Tomatoes]] and an 84 from [[Metacritic]]. Batman's newer iterations in the 2010s DCEU received mixed to negative reviews from critics. \n\nThe series' theatrically-released animated movies have a large critical disparity, with ''Mask of the Phantasm'' and ''The Lego Batman Movie'' being well-received while ''Batman: The Killing Joke'' received mixed to negative reviews.\n\n===Box office performance===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Release date\n! colspan=\"3\" | Box office revenue\n! colspan=\"2\" | Box office ranking\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Budget\n! rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n! North America\n! Other<br>territories\n! Worldwide\n! All time<br>North America\n! All time<br>worldwide\n|-\n|-\n| ''Batman (1966)''\n|  July 30, 1966\n|  $1,700,000\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"| \n| $1,700,000\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| style=\"