erkis]]\n| [[Douglas Hodge]]\n|-\n! [[James Gordon (character)|James \"Jim\" Gordon]]\n| [[Lyle Talbot]]\n| [[Neil Hamilton (actor)|Neil Hamilton]]\n| [[Pat Hingle]]\n| [[Gary Oldman]]\n| [[J. K. Simmons]]<hr>[[Jeffrey Wright]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Robin (character)|Richard \"Dick\" Grayson<br>{{small|Robin}}]]\n| [[Douglas Croft]]<hr>[[Johnny Duncan (actor)|Johnny Duncan]]\n| [[Burt Ward]]\n| [[Chris O'Donnell]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Vicki Vale]]\n| [[Poni Adams|Jane Adams]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Kim Basinger]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Joker (character)|Joker]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Cesar Romero]]\n| [[Jack Nicholson]]{{efn|Additionally, Hugo E. Blick portrays a young Joker in ''[[Batman (1989 film)|Batman]]'' (1989).}}<hr>David U. Hodges\n| [[Heath Ledger]]\n| [[Jared Leto]]\n| [[Joaquin Phoenix]]\n|-\n! [[Catwoman|Selina Kyle <br>{{small|Catwoman}}]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Lee Meriwether]]\n| [[Michelle Pfeiffer]]\n| [[Anne Hathaway]]\n| [[Zo\u00eb Kravitz]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Penguin (character)|Oswald Cobblepot<br>{{small|Penguin}}]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Burgess Meredith]]\n| [[Danny DeVito]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Colin Farrell]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Riddler]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Frank Gorshin]]\n| [[Jim Carrey]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Paul Dano]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Two-Face|Harvey Dent<br>{{small|Two-Face}}]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Billy Dee Williams]]{{ref|cameo|C}}<hr>[[Tommy Lee Jones]]\n| [[Aaron Eckhart]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Thomas Wayne]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| David Baxt<hr>Michael Scranton{{ref|cameo|C}}\n| [[Linus Roache]]\n| [[Jeffrey Dean Morgan]]\n| [[Brett Cullen]]\n|-\n! [[Martha Wayne]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| Sharon Holm<hr>Eileen Seeley{{ref|cameo|C}}\n| [[Sara Stewart]]\n| [[Lauren Cohan]]\n| Carrie Louise Putrello\n|-\n! Mayor of Gotham City\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Lee Wallace (actor)|Lee Wallace]]<hr>[[Michael Murphy (actor)|Michael Murphy]]<hr>[[George Wallace (American comedian)|George Wallace]]\n| [[N\u00e9stor Carbonell]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Sal Maroni]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| Dennis Paladino\n| [[Eric Roberts]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Bane (DC Comics)|Bane]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Robert Swenson]]{{efn|Additionally, Michael Reid MacKay portrays Antonio Diego in ''[[Batman & Robin (film)|Batman & Robin]]'', a serial killer who is ultimately transformed into Bane.}}\n| [[Tom Hardy]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Scarecrow|Jonathan Crane<br>{{small|Scarecrow}}]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Coolio]]\n| [[Cillian Murphy]]\n| colspan=\"2\" {{cEmpty}}\n|-\n! [[Carmine Falcone]]\n| colspan=\"3\" {{cEmpty}}\n| [[Tom Wilkinson]]\n| [[John Turturro]]\n| {{cEmpty}}\n|}\n\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n== Reception ==\nWith a total gross of over $4.99 billion at the global box office, the series is [[List of highest-grossing franchises and film series|eleventh highest-grossing film franchise]] of all time. Domestically, ''Batman'' films have grossed U.S. $2,783,118,504, making the franchise the fourth-highest-grossing film series in North America.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/franchises/?view=Franchise&sort=sumgross&order=DESC&p=.htm|title=Box Office Mojo Movie Franchises Index Sorted by Total Gross|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=July 10, 2013}}</ref> Critical reception of the modern films has varied throughout its different eras. [[The Dark Knight (film)|''The Dark Knight'']], from [[Christopher Nolan]]'s trilogy, is considered [[List of films considered the best|one of the best superhero movies ever]], while two entries, ''Batman and Robin'' and ''Catwoman'' are considered [[List of films considered the worst|some of the worst]]. ''The Dark Knight Rises'' is the highest-grossing ''Batman'' movie, grossing $1,081,041,287 worldwide, while ''Batman and Robin'' is the lowest-grossing film to feature Batman, at $238,207,122 worldwide. Films in the series have earned three [[Academy Awards]] (Burton's ''Batman'' for Production Design and ''The Dark Knight'' for Sound Editing and posthumous Best Supporting Actor for [[Heath Ledger]]'s performance as the Joker), one [[BAFTAs|BAFTA]] (also for Ledger), and ten [[Saturn Awards]], which honor excellence in science fiction, horror, and fantasy.\n\nOf the 1980s and 1990s, Tim Burton's films received positive critical reviews for their return of the character to a more serious portrayal, though some felt that ''Batman Returns'' was too dark. Joel Schumacher's two films received mixed to negative reviews, particularly ''Batman and Robin'', which has the lowest aggregate scores out of any film in the series. Conversely, the films in Christopher Nolan's trilogy of the 2000s and 2010s have the highest scores on review aggregation websites of the live-action feature films with ''The Dark Knight'' receiving a 94% from [[Rotten Tomatoes]] and an 84 from [[Metacritic]]. Batman's newer iterations in the 2010s DCEU received mixed to negative reviews from critics. \n\nThe series' theatrically-released animated movies have a large critical disparity, with ''Mask of the Phantasm'' and ''The Lego Batman Movie'' being well-received while ''Batman: The Killing Joke'' received mixed to negative reviews.\n\n===Box office performance===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Film\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Release date\n! colspan=\"3\" | Box office revenue\n! colspan=\"2\" | Box office ranking\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Budget\n! rowspan=\"2\" | {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n! North America\n! Other<br>territories\n! Worldwide\n! All time<br>North America\n! All time<br>worldwide\n|-\n|-\n| ''Batman (1966)''\n|  July 30, 1966\n|  $1,700,000\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"| \n| $1,700,000\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| $1.5 million \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| <ref>Solomon, Aubrey. ''T