 Awards|Saturn Award]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:left;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:214px;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Award\n! colspan=\"4\"| ''Batman: The Motion Picture Anthology''\n! colspan=\"3\"| ''The Dark Knight Trilogy''\n! colspan=\"2\"| DC Extended Universe\n|-\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Batman''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Batman Returns''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Batman Forever''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Batman & Robin''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Batman Begins''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The Dark Knight''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''The Dark Knight Rises''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice''\n! style=\"width:130px;\"| ''Justice League''\n|-\n| '''Best Fantasy Film'''\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{won}}\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Action / Adventure / Thriller Film'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{won}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Comic-to-Film Motion Picture'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Actor'''\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|\n|{{won}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Actress'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Supporting Actor'''\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|{{won}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Supporting Actress'''\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|{{won}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Director'''\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Writing'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{won}}\n|{{won}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Costumes'''\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Make-Up'''\n|{{nom}}\n|{{won}}\n|{{nom}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Special Effects'''\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|{{won}}\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| '''Best Music'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|{{nom}}\n|{{won}}\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|Speculative fiction|Film|United States}}\n* [[Batman franchise media]]\n* [[:Category:Fan films based on Batman]]\n* [[Superman in film]]\n* [[Catwoman (film)|''Catwoman'' (film)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=Guber>{{cite book |author1= Nancy Griffin |author2= Kim Masters |title= Hit & Run: How Jon Peters and Peter Guber Took Sony For A Ride In Hollywood |publisher= [[Simon & Schuster]] |year= 1997 |pages= [https://archive.org/details/hitrunhowjonpete00grif/page/158 158\u2013174] |isbn= 0-684-80931-1 |chapter= Hit Men |url= https://archive.org/details/hitrunhowjonpete00grif/page/158 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=production>{{cite news |last= Jones |first= Alan |url= http://www.batman-online.com/index.php?articles;id=2 |title= ''Batman'' in Production |publisher= [[Cinefantastique]] |pages= 75\u201388 |date= November 1989 |accessdate= May 13, 2008 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20131204224714/http://www.batman-online.com/index.php?articles;id=2 |archive-date= December 4, 2013 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Jones>{{cite news |last= Jones |first= Alan |url=http://www.1989batman.com/2013/08/vintage-magazine-article.html |title= Batman |work= [[Cinefantastique]] |pages=55\u201367 |date= November 1989 |accessdate= May 2, 2008}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Elfman>{{cite book |last=Salisbury |first=Mark |author2=[[Tim Burton]] |title= Burton on Burton |publisher= Faber and Faber |year= 2006 |location= London |pages= 70\u201383 |chapter= Batman |isbn= 0-571-22926-3}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.boxofficemojo.com/showdowns/chart/?id=batmanvs.htm ''Batman'' franchise overview] at [[Box Office Mojo]]\n* {{IMDb title|1345836|The Dark Knight Rises}}\n* [http://behindbatman.weebly.com/ Behind Batman: Public Domain Analysis of the Film Franchise]\n\n{{Batman in film}}\n{{Batman in popular media}}\n{{DC Comics films}}\n{{Batman}}\n\n{{Good article}}\n\n<!--Primary grouping categories-->\n\n[[Category:Film series introduced in 1943]]\n[[Category:Batman films| ]]\n", "name_user": "ScottSullivan1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFilms", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batman_in_film"}
{"title_page": "Natalia Dyer", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Natalia Dyer\n| image              = Natalia Dyer by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Dyer at the 2017 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Natalia Danielle Dyer\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1995|1|13}}<!-- Do NOT change birth year. This has been discussed at length. See talk page for details -->{{refn|group=Note|name=\"birth year\"}}\n| birth_place        = [[Nashville, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actress\n| years_active       = 2008\u2013present\n\n}}\n\n'''Natalia Danielle Dyer''' (born January 13, 1995<!-- Do NOT change birth year. This has been discussed at length. See talk page for details -->)<ref>{{cite newspaper|title=Births|date=February 4, 1995|work=[[The Tennessean]]|page=4D|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/33938322/natalia_danielle_dyer_birth_notice/|accessdate=16 July 2019|via=Newspapers.com|quote=Allen Miles and Karen Lea have named their daughter, born Jan. 13 at Vanderbilt Hospital, Natalia Danielle Dyer.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Donnell |first1=Evans |title=Review: Circle Players 'Mockingbird' revival promising, but suffers from pacing |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/33942174/ |work=[[The Tennessean]] |date=March 9, 2004 |via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>{{refn|group=Note|name=\"birth year\"|Some sources give her birth year as 1997, but this is contradicted by the balance of evidence.}} is an American actress. She is best known for her starring role as [[Nancy Wheeler]] in the [[Netflix]] science fiction horror series ''[[Stranger Things]]'' (2016\u2013present).\n\n==Early life and education ==\nDyer was born and raised in Nashville, Tennessee, graduating from the performing arts high school [[Nashville School of the Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/entertainment/2016/08/25/stranger-things-star-nashville-native/89299532/|title=Before 'Stranger Things,' actress Natalia Dyer got her start at Nashville's TPAC|author=Paulson, Dave|date=September 6, 2016|publisher=Tennessean}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nDyer's first screen role was as Clarissa Granger in ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'' in 2009. In 2011, she appeared in ''[[The Greening of Whitney Brown]]''. Dyer then starred in the [[Independent film|indie film]] ''[[I Believe in Unicorns]]'', which premiered in 2014 at [[South by Southwest|SXSW]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/173630-whos-nancy-on-stranger-things-natalia-dyers-performance-is-one-of-the-shows-best|title=Who's Nancy On 'Stranger Things'? Natalia Dyer's Performance Is One Of The Show's Best|last=Flynn|first=Caitlin|date=July 20, 2016|website=www.bustle.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romper.com/p/who-plays-nancy-wheeler-on-stranger-things-natalia-dyer-got-her-start-in-disney-14064|title=Who Plays Nancy Wheeler On 'Stranger Things'? Natalia Dyer Got Her Start In Disney|last=Bobic|first=Chrissy}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Dyer was cast as [[Nancy Wheeler (character)|Nancy Wheeler]] in the Netflix series ''[[Stranger Things (TV series)|Stranger Things]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/4459211/stranger-things-nancy-jonathan-interview/|title=Stranger Things Actor Kills All Hope for Jonathan and Nancy|last=Hoffman|first=Ashley|website=TIME.com|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref> In 2019, Dyer starred as Coco in the Netflix [[Horror film|horror]] film ''[[Velvet Buzzsaw]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/dan-gilroy-jake-gyllenhaal-movie-cast-natalia-dyer-daveed-digs-john-malkovich-1202336577/|title=New Dan Gilroy-Jake Gyllenhaal Movie Finalizes Cast\n|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=February 4, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/au/entertainment/movies/stranger-things-star-natalia-dyer-on-her-exciting-role-in-velvet-buzzsaw-37760050.html|title=Stranger Things star Natalia Dyer on her 'exciting' role in Velvet Buzzsaw|last=Southern|first=Kieran|publisher=[[Irish Independent]]|date=January 29, 2019|accessdate=February 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDyer moved to New York City and enrolled at [[NYU]] in 2013, studying at the [[Gallatin School of Individualized Study]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/stranger-thingss-natalia-dyer-explains-why-nancy-wheeler-isnt-your-average-big-sister |title=Stranger Things's Natalia Dyer Explains Why Nancy Wheeler Isn't Your Average Big Sister |first=Ella |last=Ceron |date=October 3, 2016 |website=[[Teen Vogue]] |accessdate=July 23, 2017}}</ref> Since 2016, she has been in a relationship with her ''Stranger Things'' co-star [[Charlie Heaton]], who plays Nancy's boyfriend Jonathan Byers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Natalia Dyer And Charlie Heaton From Stranger Things Dating: Their Relationship Timeline Revealed|date=3 July 2019|work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/tv-film/stranger-things/natalia-dyer-charlie-heaton-relationship-timeline/|accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n===Film===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]''\n|Clarissa Granger\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|''Too Sunny for Santa''\n|Janie\n|Short film<ref name=\"Lee\">{{cite news |last1=Lee |first1=Tena |title=Tachoir's film premieres in Nashville |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/34113352/too_sunny_for_santa_2/ |work=Hendersonville Star News |date=April 16, 2010 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[The Greening of Whitney Brown]]''\n|Lily\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Blue Like Jazz (film)|Blue Like Jazz]]''\n|Grace\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[Don't Let Me Go (film)|Don't Let Me Go]]''\n|Banshee\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2014\n|''[[I Believe in Unicorns]]''<ref name=\"Paulson\">{{cite news |last1=Paulson |first1=Dave |title=Nashville Film Festival Looks Near and Far |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/33946446/nashville_film_festival_2014_2/ |work=[[The Tennessean]] |date=April 16, 2014 |language=en}}</ref>\n|Davina\n|\n|-\n|''The City at Night''\n|Adeline\n|Short film\n|-\n|2015\n|''Till Dark''\n|Lucy\n|Short film\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Long Nights Short Mornings]]''\n|Marie\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''Yes, God, Yes''\n|Alice\n|Short film\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2018\n|''[[Mountain Rest (film)|Mountain Rest]]''\n|Clara\n|\n|-\n|''After Her''\n|Hailey\n|Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=5|2019\n| ''[[After Darkness (2019 film)|After Darkness]]''\n|Clara\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Velvet Buzzsaw]]''\n|Coco\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Yes, God, Yes]]''\n|Alice\n|\n|-\n| ''The Nearest Human Being''<ref>{{cite web|last=Wynne|first=Kelly|title=HERE'S EVERYTHING THE 'STRANGER THINGS' CAST IS DOING AFTER SEASON 3|date=7 March 2019|publisher=[[Newsweek]]|url=https://www.newsweek.com/stranger-things-cast-plans-projects-after-season-3-1447398?amp=1|accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n| Monique\n|\n|-\n|''[[Tuscaloosa (film)|Tuscaloosa]]''\n|Virginia\n|\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Things Heard and Seen]]''\n|\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n| ''[[Stranger Things]]''\n|[[Nancy Wheeler]]\n| <!-- DO NOT CHANGE THIS TO 25 EPISODES, DYER WAS ABSENT FOR THE STAND ALONE EPISODE \u2014 SEASON 2 EPISODE 7: THE LOST SISTER -->\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n!Ref\n|-\n|2018\n|\"[[Wild Love (James Bay song)|Wild Love]]\"\n|[[James Bay (singer)|James Bay]]\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8208031/james-bay-wild-love-video-stranger-things-natalia-dyer|title='Stranger Things' Star Natalia Dyer Only Has Eyes for James Bay in 'Wild Love' Video: Watch|work=Billboard|access-date=2018-03-23}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nominated work\n! Award\n! Category\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"4\"| ''[[Stranger Things]]''\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2016/12/14/2017-sag-awards-nominations|title=SAG Awards nominations 2017: See the full list|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Joely|last=Nolfi|date=December 14, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Young Artist Awards]]\n| [[38th Young Artist Awards#Best Performance in a Digital TV Series or Film|Best Performance in a Digital TV Series or Film \u2014 Teen Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n| \n|-\n| Gold Derby Awards\n| Best Ensemble of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goldderby.com/article/2017/2017-gold-derby-tv-awards-winners-big-little-lies-news-357924086/ |title=2017 Gold Derby TV Awards winners: 'Big Little Lies' and 'SNL' sweep, while 'Stranger Things' takes Best Drama |last=Dixon |first=Marcus James |last2=Montgomery |first2=Daniel |work=[[Gold Derby]] |date=September 6, 2017 |access-date=July 8, 2019 |publisher=[[Penske Business Media, LLC.]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/sag-awards-stunt-nominees-2018-john-bernecker-walking-dead-1202239125/ |title=SAG Awards' Stunt Ensemble Nominees Include Fallen 'Walking Dead' Stuntman |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=January 21, 2018 |access-date=July 8, 2019 |publisher=[[Penske Business Media, LLC.]]}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=Note}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|id=3034501}}\n\n{{ScreenActorsGuildAwards EnsembleTVDrama 2010\u20132019}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dyer, Natalia}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Nashville, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:New York University Gallatin School of Individualized Study alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Natalia Dyer\n| image              = Natalia Dyer by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| alt                = \n| caption            = Dyer at the 2017 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Natalia Danielle Dyer\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1995|1|13}}<!-- Do NOT change birth year. This has been discussed at length. See talk page for details -->{{refn|group=Note|name=\"birth year\"}}\n| birth_place        = [[Nashville, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actress\n| years_active       = 2008\u2013present\n\n}}\n\n'''Natalia Danielle Dyer''' (born January 13, 1995<!-- Do NOT change birth year. This has been discussed at length. See talk page for details -->)<ref>{{cite newspaper|title=Births|date=February 4, 1995|work=[[The Tennessean]]|page=4D|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/33938322/natalia_danielle_dyer_birth_notice/|accessdate=16 July 2019|via=Newspapers.com|quote=Allen Miles and Karen Lea have named their daughter, born Jan. 13 at Vanderbilt Hospital, Natalia Danielle Dyer.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Donnell |first1=Evans |title=Review: Circle Players 'Mockingbird' revival promising, but suffers from pacing |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/33942174/ |work=[[The Tennessean]] |date=March 9, 2004 |via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>{{refn|group=Note|name=\"birth year\"|Some sources give her birth year as 1997, but this is contradicted by the balance of evidence.}} is an American actress. She is best known for her starring role as [[Nancy Wheeler (character)|Nancy Wheeler]] in the [[Netflix]] science fiction horror series ''[[Stranger Things]]'' (2016\u2013present).\n\n==Early life and education ==\nDyer was born and raised in Nashville, Tennessee, graduating from the performing arts high school [[Nashville School of the Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/entertainment/2016/08/25/stranger-things-star-nashville-native/89299532/|title=Before 'Stranger Things,' actress Natalia Dyer got her start at Nashville's TPAC|author=Paulson, Dave|date=September 6, 2016|publisher=Tennessean}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nDyer's first screen role was as Clarissa Granger in ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'' in 2009. In 2011, she appeared in ''[[The Greening of Whitney Brown]]''. Dyer then starred in the [[Independent film|indie film]] ''[[I Believe in Unicorns]]'', which premiered in 2014 at [[South by Southwest|SXSW]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bustle.com/articles/173630-whos-nancy-on-stranger-things-natalia-dyers-performance-is-one-of-the-shows-best|title=Who's Nancy On 'Stranger Things'? Natalia Dyer's Performance Is One Of The Show's Best|last=Flynn|first=Caitlin|date=July 20, 2016|website=www.bustle.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.romper.com/p/who-plays-nancy-wheeler-on-stranger-things-natalia-dyer-got-her-start-in-disney-14064|title=Who Plays Nancy Wheeler On 'Stranger Things'? Natalia Dyer Got Her Start In Disney|last=Bobic|first=Chrissy}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Dyer was cast as [[Nancy Wheeler (character)|Nancy Wheeler]] in the Netflix series ''[[Stranger Things (TV series)|Stranger Things]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/4459211/stranger-things-nancy-jonathan-interview/|title=Stranger Things Actor Kills All Hope for Jonathan and Nancy|last=Hoffman|first=Ashley|website=TIME.com|access-date=2016-09-18}}</ref> In 2019, Dyer starred as Coco in the Netflix [[Horror film|horror]] film ''[[Velvet Buzzsaw]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/dan-gilroy-jake-gyllenhaal-movie-cast-natalia-dyer-daveed-digs-john-malkovich-1202336577/|title=New Dan Gilroy-Jake Gyllenhaal Movie Finalizes Cast\n|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=February 4, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/au/entertainment/movies/stranger-things-star-natalia-dyer-on-her-exciting-role-in-velvet-buzzsaw-37760050.html|title=Stranger Things star Natalia Dyer on her 'exciting' role in Velvet Buzzsaw|last=Southern|first=Kieran|publisher=[[Irish Independent]]|date=January 29, 2019|accessdate=February 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDyer moved to New York City and enrolled at [[NYU]] in 2013, studying at the [[Gallatin School of Individualized Study]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/stranger-thingss-natalia-dyer-explains-why-nancy-wheeler-isnt-your-average-big-sister |title=Stranger Things's Natalia Dyer Explains Why Nancy Wheeler Isn't Your Average Big Sister |first=Ella |last=Ceron |date=October 3, 2016 |website=[[Teen Vogue]] |accessdate=July 23, 2017}}</ref> Since 2016, she has been in a relationship with her ''Stranger Things'' co-star [[Charlie Heaton]], who plays Nancy's boyfriend Jonathan Byers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Natalia Dyer And Charlie Heaton From Stranger Things Dating: Their Relationship Timeline Revealed|date=3 July 2019|work=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital]]|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/news/tv-film/stranger-things/natalia-dyer-charlie-heaton-relationship-timeline/|accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n===Film===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]''\n|Clarissa Granger\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|''Too Sunny for Santa''\n|Janie\n|Short film<ref name=\"Lee\">{{cite news |last1=Lee |first1=Tena |title=Tachoir's film premieres in Nashville |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/34113352/too_sunny_for_santa_2/ |work=Hendersonville Star News |date=April 16, 2010 |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[The Greening of Whitney Brown]]''\n|Lily\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''[[Blue Like Jazz (film)|Blue Like Jazz]]''\n|Grace\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[